description: An electronic file is an information content entity which conforms to a specification or format and which is meant to hold data and information in digital form, accessible to software agents. In RD3: Individuals files stored in the sandbox environments. Files are linked to subjects, samples, and experiments, as well as with EGA accession number.
Recommended practice is to identify the resource by means of a string conforming to an identification system. An unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.
A 32-character hexadecimal number that is computed on a file.
The name (or part of a name) of a file (of any type), i.e. the literal identifier for an electronic file.
A computer which provides some service for other computers connected to it via a network.
A file path is an identifier for a file in a file system or network.
A digital resource format (e.g. BAM, FastQ, gVCF, phenopacket, BED)
profiles: Beacon v2 EMX2 add-on, RD3, DCAT files add-on

description: Beacon v2 Analyses
Beacon v2 Biosamples
Beacon v2 Cohorts
One or more subject identifier associated with a file
Beacon v2 Runs
The literal identifier for an electronic file (EGA Accession number).
One more more sample identifier associated with a file
Identifier of the corresponding record in the labinfo table
One or more Solve-RD releases that indicate when the record was first introduced into RD3 or when it was updated.
The location of the file on Fender
The location of the file on Gearshift
Reference to the study or studies in which this person participates.
A group of individuals, identified by a common characteristic.
Reference to the dataset or datasets in which this person was assigned to.
A written explanation, observation or criticism added to textual material.
A person is an object that has certain capacities or attributes constituting personhood. In RD3: researcher or contactperson involved in the study and/or affliated with organisation.
A unique symbol that establishes identity of the qualified person.
A personal name is a name to identify an individual person and usually comprises of a first name and a last name.
A backup sequence of characters used to identify an entity.
A first name is a name that denotes a specific individual between members of a group of individuals, whose members usually share the same surname.
A middle name is a name assigned to an individual that is not the first or last name.
A last name (surname) is a name added to a given name and is part of a personal name and is often the family name.
An email address is an identifier to send mail to particular electronic mailbox of a contact person or organization.
The most significant institute associated to this person.
